        "timestamp": "2019-11-13 18:57:53.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nThis is strange, it builds successfully on my local machine. This is the error in Jenkins report: \nAppcLcmCommonHeaderTest.testAppcLcmCommonHeaderConstructor:35 expected:<AppcLcmCommonHeader(timeStamp=2019-11-13T18:37:54.081Z, apiVer=2.00, originatorId=Policy, requestId=6fad2f65-b37b-4014-874a-75f3059e588e, subRequestId=1, flags={})> but was:<AppcLcmCommonHeader(timeStamp=2019-11-13T18:37:54.082Z, apiVer=2.00, originatorId=Policy, requestId=6fad2f65-b37b-4014-874a-75f3059e588e, subRequestId=1, flags={})>\n\nI also ran this individual test, it runs fine on my machine. Any suggestions how to fix this - it is expecting a different timestamp. \nThanks!",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "92116e7c478c0a7a0ec5a84f3cca6641bfeecf2f",
