        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-11-13 19:28:53.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> This is strange, it builds successfully on my local machine. This\n > is the error in Jenkins report:\n > AppcLcmCommonHeaderTest.testAppcLcmCommonHeaderConstructor:35\n > expected:<AppcLcmCommonHeader(timeStamp=2019-11-13T18:37:54.081Z,\n > apiVer=2.00, originatorId=Policy, requestId=6fad2f65-b37b-4014-874a-75f3059e588e,\n > subRequestId=1, flags={})> but was:<AppcLcmCommonHeader(timeStamp=2019-11-13T18:37:54.082Z,\n > apiVer=2.00, originatorId=Policy, requestId=6fad2f65-b37b-4014-874a-75f3059e588e,\n > subRequestId=1, flags={})>\n > \n > I also ran this individual test, it runs fine on my machine. Any\n > suggestions how to fix this - it is expecting a different\n > timestamp.\n > Thanks!\n\nOne possibility is to modify the copy constructor to also copy the timestamp.  Since it's supposed to be a \"copy\", this may be the \"right\" behavior.  Another alternative would be to invoke toString() on both, do a replaceFirst(\"timeStamp=[^,]*\", \"\"), and then compare the resulting strings",
